@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@user01 = user01
@user02 = user02

### TC_SEC_001 - SQL Injection payload at Cart productId
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/cart/add
X-USER-ID: {{user01}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": "P001' OR '1'='1",
  "quantity": 1
}

### TC_SEC_002 - SQL Injection payload at Order ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/ORD-001%27%20OR%20%271%27%3D%271

### Prepare data - Create cart for user01
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/cart/add
X-USER-ID: {{user01}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": "P001",
  "quantity": 1
}

### TC_SEC_004A - Read cart as user01
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/cart
X-USER-ID: {{user01}}

### TC_SEC_004B - IDOR check: read cart after changing X-USER-ID manually
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/cart
X-USER-ID: {{user02}}

### TC_SEC_005 - Missing Authorization: create order without Authorization and without X-USER-ID
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "items": [
    {
      "productId": "P002",
      "quantity": 1
    }
  ],
  "couponCode": "SALE10",
  "shippingFee": 50000,
  "shippingAddress": "No auth address",
  "paymentMethod": "COD"
}

### TC_SEC_003 - XSS payload in shippingAddress
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
X-USER-ID: {{user01}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "items": [
    {
      "productId": "P002",
      "quantity": 1
    }
  ],
  "couponCode": "SALE10",
  "shippingFee": 50000,
  "shippingAddress": "<script>alert('xss')</script>",
  "paymentMethod": "COD"
}

### TC_SEC_006 - CSRF/CORS simulation with unexpected Origin
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/cart/add
Origin: http://evil.localhost
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": "P001",
  "quantity": 1
}

### TC_SEC_007A - Input validation: negative quantity
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/cart/add
X-USER-ID: {{user01}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": "P001",
  "quantity": -1
}

### TC_SEC_007B - Input validation: quantity exceeds stock
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/cart/add
X-USER-ID: {{user01}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "productId": "P001",
  "quantity": 999999999
}
